  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Post-Tailwind Migration Menu Visibility and Layout Issues\n\nAfter migrating to Tailwind CSS, the menu component is broken with visibility and layout problems that need to be resolved.\n\nRequirements:\n- Restore full menu visibility - investigate why menu elements are hidden or not rendering\n- Fix menu layout structure - identify and correct misaligned or improperly positioned elements\n- Review Tailwind class replacements for menu components to ensure proper styling migration\n- Check for conflicting CSS rules between legacy styles and new Tailwind classes\n- Verify responsive behavior across different screen sizes\n- Test menu interactions (hover states, dropdowns, active states, transitions)\n- Ensure menu positioning (fixed, absolute, sticky) is correctly implemented with Tailwind utilities\n- Check z-index layering to ensure menu appears above other content when needed\n- Validate that all menu items are accessible and clickable\n- Review any JavaScript that manipulates menu classes to ensure compatibility with Tailwind\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Menu behavior on mobile vs desktop viewports\n- Menu state when page loads vs after user interaction\n- Nested submenu items if present\n- Menu appearance in different browser environments",
